The paper deals with a problem of consensus on preference rankings, which is a topic in social choice theory. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also proposes algorithms to solve the problem, which suggests that it could belong to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with fault tolerance in distributed systems, which could make it relevant to the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
